        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 10:17PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 1017 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Hartford to 6 miles north of Salem to
Greenwich. Movement was east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Arlington, Salem, Manchester, Granville, Hartford, Dorset, Greenwich,
Manchester Center, Porter, Schuylerville, Sunderland, Rupert, Fort
Ann, Sandgate, Peru, Glastenbury, Cossayuna, Beartown, Chiselville,
and Center Falls.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
